title: Favorite social networks of U.S. teens 2012 to 2019
summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 13 different Responses for 8 groups Snapchat, Instagram, Twitter, Facebook, Tumblr, Pinterest, Google+, and Other that are presented on the X-axis.
Out of all 8 groups, Snapchat had the highest SOME LABEL in Response Fall 2017 and Snapchat had the lowest SOME LABEL in Response Fall 2012.
Among all the Responses, Snapchat had the highest SOME LABEL 47.0 in Response Fall 2017 and lowest value 0.0 in Response Fall 2012.
Response Fall 2017 and Fall 2012 had the biggest gap of 46.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for Snapchat.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 13 different Responses on X-axis for 8 groups Snapchat, Instagram, Twitter, Facebook, Tumblr, Pinterest, Google+, and Other. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
Response Fall 2017 had the maximum SOME LABEL among all 8 groups, and it was for Snapchat. The minimum SOME LABEL was observed in Response Fall 2012 for Snapchat.
In Response Fall 2017, Snapchat had the highest SOME LABEL among all 13 Responses and it has the lowest SOME LABEL in Response Fall 2012.
The maximum SOME LABEL for Snapchat that was found in Response Fall 2017 was 47.0 times larger than the minimum SOME LABEL observed in Response Fall 2012.
Among all 8 groups, Snapchat had the gap of 47.0 between the maximum and minimum SOME LABEL observed in Response Fall 2017 and Fall 2012 respectively.

In Response Fall 2017, Snapchat had the highest SOME LABEL 47.0 among the 8 groups and in Fall 2012, Snapchat had the lowest SOME LABEL 0.0. The second highest SOME LABEL 5.0 was observed for Snapchat in Response Fall 2017.

On average, the Response Fall 2013 had the highest SOME LABEL for all 8 groups Snapchat, Instagram, Twitter, Facebook, Tumblr, Pinterest, Google+, and Other. Whereas Spring 2017 had the lowest average SOME LABEL.
